  "fun_fact": "June 21 is Show Your Stripes Day — a global moment to share the warming stripes. Climate scientist Ed Hawkins created these deceptively simple stripes in 2018: each stripe is one year, blue for cooler, red for warmer. The stripes turned a century of temperature data into something anyone could easily see. You can find the stripes for your country or city: <a href=\"https://showyourstripes.info/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Show your stripes</a>",
